{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":1,"author":{"id":"e6e37a604213073fe002068791f779e5d644f9dd"},"timestamp":1577834451,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWU1NDQyODY3Nzc=","github-url":"https://github.com/DFHack/dfhack/issues/1478","origin":"github"},"title":"digfort throws up error if number of lines is longer than number of squares along y axis","message":"If the number of lines in the .csv file is greater than the total number of squares along the y axis, digfort throws an error and doesn't designate anything. This causes problems if you are designating large areas across many z levels.\n\nYou can successfully designate large files if you comment out this code, but it probably causes other issues:\n\n\nif x \u003c 0 or y \u003c 0 or x+max_x \u003e= map.x_count or y+max_y \u003e= map.y_count\n    max_x = max_x + x + 1\n    max_y = max_y + y + 1\n    raise \"Position would designate outside map limits. Selected limits are from (#{x+1}, #{y+1}) to (#{max_x},#{max_y})\"\n\nend","files":null}]}